WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:01.234
.

00:01.601 --> 00:02.503
- Hey, you have
a female attempted suicide?

00:03.971 --> 00:05.639
- Yeah, she just came in.

00:05.639 --> 00:08.141
- She's alive, barely.

00:08.141 --> 00:09.543
Gas inhalation.

00:09.543 --> 00:11.079
- We gotta get her to Med
right now.

00:11.079 --> 00:12.813
- Come on, let's go.

00:12.813 --> 00:14.448
- What is it about?

00:14.448 --> 00:17.085
- We need to be sure there's
nothing more going on here.

00:17.085 --> 00:20.188
- That attempted suicide?

00:20.188 --> 00:21.822
Dr. Charles--
he's not buying it.

00:21.822 --> 00:23.891
- What's not to buy?
You heard the report.

00:25.359 --> 00:28.696
- Today, three women,
all cancer-free,

00:28.696 --> 00:30.198
overdosed on chemo.

00:30.198 --> 00:31.699
- Clear.
- Clear.

00:31.699 --> 00:35.169
- Do you think a doctor's giving
false diagnoses and overdosing?

00:35.169 --> 00:37.505
- The police are on their way.

00:39.039 --> 00:42.110
- Jessica Pope, Carol Shepperd,
Dani Frank.

00:42.110 --> 00:44.011
Each brought independently
to Med

00:44.011 --> 00:45.813
with no connection
between 'em

00:45.813 --> 00:49.383
except an overdose of chemo
for a cancer they don't have.

00:49.383 --> 00:51.752
I wanna know
who prescribed that stuff.

00:51.752 --> 00:53.521
- 51 said
that the gas explosion

00:53.521 --> 00:55.889
in Jessica's apartment
caused a flashover.

00:55.889 --> 00:57.391
So there is nothing left
but char.

00:57.391 --> 00:59.660
There's no phone,
no laptop, no datebook.

00:59.660 --> 01:01.262
Nothing.
- No doctor's name.

01:01.262 --> 01:03.030
- We talked
to Dani Frank's girlfriend.

01:03.030 --> 01:04.364
They hadn't been dating
that long.

01:04.364 --> 01:05.633
She didn't know Dani's doctor.

01:05.633 --> 01:07.668
But she did say that
Dani was doing better

01:07.668 --> 01:09.570
until she took a turn,

01:09.570 --> 01:11.139
and when she confronted
her doctor about it

01:11.139 --> 01:13.040
he put her
on an experimental protocol

01:13.040 --> 01:14.408
that was supposed to beat it.

01:16.377 --> 01:17.678
- Sorry to interrupt.

01:17.678 --> 01:19.147
A new patient just
rolled into the ED.

01:19.147 --> 01:22.683
Unconscious, pancytopenic
just like the others.

01:22.683 --> 01:24.418
Look, I don't know
if this is legal,

01:24.418 --> 01:26.187
but, right now,
I really don't care.

01:26.187 --> 01:27.788
That's her stuff.
Have at it.

01:27.788 --> 01:29.323
- Thank you.
- All right.

01:33.561 --> 01:37.064
- All right, Leah Kamen,
42, lives in Edgewater.

01:37.064 --> 01:39.066
- She's a shift manager
at a telemarketing firm.

01:39.066 --> 01:40.734
- Insurance card.
I'll call the company,

01:40.734 --> 01:42.603
see if they got the name
of the doctor

01:42.603 --> 01:43.771
who submitted the claim.

01:43.771 --> 01:45.506
- Hey, is there any way
to trace the chemicals

01:45.506 --> 01:47.641
in their system back
to a specific manufacturer?

01:47.641 --> 01:50.344
- A mass spectrometry test
was performed on Jessica.

01:50.344 --> 01:51.612
We can order the same
for the others.

01:51.612 --> 01:53.181
There're only
a few manufacturers.

01:53.181 --> 01:54.682
- Will you do it, please?
- Yep.

01:54.682 --> 01:55.883
- Thanks.

01:55.883 --> 01:59.620
- Uh, Leah has Dani Frank,
Carol Shepperd,

01:59.620 --> 02:01.722
and Jessica Pope
as contacts on her phone.

02:01.722 --> 02:03.291
- All our victims
knew each other.

02:03.291 --> 02:04.592
- Yeah, looks like that.

02:04.592 --> 02:06.594
- Huh...
- Great. Thanks.

02:06.594 --> 02:09.263
I got a name.
Dr. Dean Reybold.

02:09.263 --> 02:11.799
[dramatic music]

02:11.799 --> 02:19.072
*

02:19.072 --> 02:21.609
- Hank.
- Hey...

02:21.609 --> 02:23.711
Al.

02:23.711 --> 02:25.213
What's going on?

02:25.213 --> 02:27.415
- [whispers]
Oh, man...

02:27.415 --> 02:29.283
- Hank. Hank.

02:29.283 --> 02:31.084
Hey, you can't go.

02:31.084 --> 02:33.221
- The hell I can't.

02:33.221 --> 02:35.623
- If you show up,
Reybold is gonna shut down.

02:35.623 --> 02:38.459
He doesn't know me.
I will take Jay.

02:38.459 --> 02:41.495
We will find out if he's
the one overdosing these women.

02:43.497 --> 02:45.499
Al...
- We'll look into the victim

02:45.499 --> 02:47.968
and then talk to Goodwin.

02:47.968 --> 02:50.238
Just you and me.
Right?

02:51.705 --> 02:55.709
- It's six years since I've
heard the name Dean Reybold.

02:55.709 --> 02:57.978
Six years since...

02:57.978 --> 03:00.881
- I know.

03:00.881 --> 03:04.852
- He was the last cancer doctor
Camille went to,

03:04.852 --> 03:06.254
and if he's the one
doing this--

03:06.254 --> 03:09.723
- If he's the one doing this,
we're gonna nail him.

03:11.000 --> 03:17.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:18.299 --> 03:18.432
.

03:21.134 --> 03:21.769
- I'm sorry to keep you
waiting.

03:23.036 --> 03:26.674
Uh, my receptionist said
you were here about Leah.

03:26.674 --> 03:28.008
Brave woman.

03:28.008 --> 03:30.511
- That's right,
and Dani Frank, Jessica Pope,

03:30.511 --> 03:31.945
and Carol Shepperd as well.

03:31.945 --> 03:33.881
- Did something happen to them?

03:33.881 --> 03:35.983
- In the last 24 hours,
they've all shown up

03:35.983 --> 03:39.086
at Chicago Med
flooded with chemo.

03:39.086 --> 03:40.721
Dani's dead,

03:40.721 --> 03:42.456
and the other three
are in comas.

03:44.358 --> 03:46.527
- [sighs]

03:46.527 --> 03:49.530
[clears throat]

03:49.530 --> 03:50.831
Uh...

03:50.831 --> 03:54.302
They teach you...a lot about
the body in medical school,

03:54.302 --> 03:57.004
but what they don't
spend enough time on

03:57.004 --> 03:59.607
is teaching you
how to deal with loss.

03:59.607 --> 04:02.009
You get attached
to your patients.

04:02.009 --> 04:04.545
They're fighters,
and you fight with them,

04:04.545 --> 04:06.814
but with oncology,
you rarely win.

04:06.814 --> 04:09.317
- So, you treated
all of them?

04:09.317 --> 04:11.184
- I did--I am.

04:11.184 --> 04:14.021
- When was the last time
you met with these women?

04:14.021 --> 04:16.189
- I would have
to check their files.

04:16.189 --> 04:18.625
- Do you mind if we take
a look at those files?

04:18.625 --> 04:21.228
- Uh, I don't,
but the state does.

04:21.228 --> 04:23.697
I can't give 'em to you
unless you have a warrant,

04:23.697 --> 04:25.433
but the moment you do,
they're yours.

04:25.433 --> 04:27.000
I will hand them over
personally.

04:27.000 --> 04:28.336
- Why don't we drop the whole

04:28.336 --> 04:30.170
"I'm a fighter
for my patients" act,

04:30.170 --> 04:32.005
all right?

04:32.005 --> 04:34.074
We know you
mistreat your patients,

04:34.074 --> 04:36.544
and we know you did something
to these four women.

04:36.544 --> 04:38.346
- Yes, I helped them.

04:38.346 --> 04:39.713
- By poisoning them?

04:39.713 --> 04:41.915
- That's what chemotherapy is,
Detective.

04:41.915 --> 04:43.517
You poison cancer cells.

04:43.517 --> 04:45.519
If you don't understand
the most--

04:45.519 --> 04:47.988
- I understand
exactly what you did.

04:47.988 --> 04:49.557
- You know what, we're gonna be
back with a warrant.

04:49.557 --> 04:51.459
Thank you.

04:51.459 --> 04:53.694
- You know I'm happy to help
in any way I can.

04:56.730 --> 04:57.931
- Thanks for coming.

04:57.931 --> 04:59.800
- A little notice
would have been nice.

04:59.800 --> 05:01.902
- We're moving like
a bullet train on this one.

05:01.902 --> 05:03.937
- Well you pulled me out of
a jerk-off awards banquet,

05:03.937 --> 05:05.373
so I can't complain.

05:05.373 --> 05:07.508
Got a locker room
I could use to change?

05:07.508 --> 05:09.176
- Whatever you need,
Counselor.

05:17.385 --> 05:19.387
- Uh, Sarge, is there
anything more on the--

05:19.387 --> 05:22.155
- Burgess,
you remember Detective Stark

05:22.155 --> 05:24.958
from Area Central,
Violent Crimes, don't you?

05:24.958 --> 05:27.495
Lead detective
on Roman's shooting?

05:27.495 --> 05:29.730
- Right.
It's good to see you, Detective.

05:29.730 --> 05:31.399
I just wanted to say again

05:31.399 --> 05:33.401
how useful I can be
to your investigation--

05:33.401 --> 05:36.136
- Did something change
since I took your statement,

05:36.136 --> 05:38.271
or did you
actually see something?

05:38.271 --> 05:41.409
- Okay, the victim's ex-wife
said she saw a gun.

05:41.409 --> 05:43.143
I mean, there's evidence
of her being beaten with it.

05:43.143 --> 05:45.779
- The hospital report's
inconclusive,

05:45.779 --> 05:47.715
and Officer Roman underwent

05:47.715 --> 05:50.984
a painful medical procedure
to help this woman's child.

05:50.984 --> 05:53.821
So their relationship is...
suspect.

05:53.821 --> 05:55.255
- Okay, what is
your agenda here?

05:55.255 --> 05:56.657
Because
from where I'm standing,

05:56.657 --> 05:58.258
you look like you want
to do anything

05:58.258 --> 05:59.693
but help a jammed-up cop

05:59.693 --> 06:02.129
who wears the same badge as you,
Detective.

06:02.129 --> 06:03.831
- I have statements
from officers

06:03.831 --> 06:05.733
who canvassed neighbors,
yards, and alleys,

06:05.733 --> 06:07.835
and no gun has been found.

06:07.835 --> 06:10.538
Stay out of my investigation.

06:13.807 --> 06:15.976
- Hey.
- Thanks.

06:15.976 --> 06:18.446
- The guy's a prick.
What's the word?

06:18.446 --> 06:20.147
- I'm on ice
till they figure this out.

06:20.147 --> 06:21.582
I shouldn't even be
talking to you.

06:21.582 --> 06:23.316
- What can I do?
- You heard him.

06:23.316 --> 06:25.853
Nothing.
I'll see you later.

06:27.320 --> 06:29.156
- Burgess.

06:29.156 --> 06:30.724
Burgess.

06:30.724 --> 06:32.760
Burgess!
Get over here.

06:34.094 --> 06:35.596
- What?
- You're on your own today.

06:35.596 --> 06:38.031
- What?
- No partner. No assignment.

06:38.031 --> 06:40.333
I want you out there
patrolling wherever you want,

06:40.333 --> 06:42.603
and if that happens to be
in a neighborhood

06:42.603 --> 06:44.472
where a gun went missing,
well...

06:44.472 --> 06:47.007
I don't know
anything about that.

06:47.007 --> 06:49.042
- Thank you, Sergeant.

06:53.313 --> 06:55.282
- We'll need documents,
invoices.

06:55.282 --> 06:58.519
If the doctor ordered medicine
overseas, the source country.

06:58.519 --> 07:00.521
Every piece of evidence counts.

07:00.521 --> 07:04.091
I need proof that Reybold
acted with criminal intent.

07:04.091 --> 07:07.160
I need evidence he knew his
actions could result in harm,

07:07.160 --> 07:08.929
but he acted anyway.

07:08.929 --> 07:12.265
Until you have that...
no arrests.

07:12.265 --> 07:15.068
Is that clear?

07:15.068 --> 07:16.504
- Let's do it.

07:16.504 --> 07:19.507
[tense music]

07:19.507 --> 07:27.515
*

07:34.421 --> 07:36.223
Antonio, Atwater.

07:41.361 --> 07:44.397
[paper shredder whining]

07:47.167 --> 07:48.268
- Chicago PD!

07:48.268 --> 07:50.403
Ma'am, step away
from the shredder.

07:50.403 --> 07:51.939
I need you to step away
from the--

07:51.939 --> 07:53.340
Come on, come on, come on.
Set it down.

07:53.340 --> 07:54.808
Set it down.

07:54.808 --> 07:56.409
- Sergeant,
we're holding one here

07:56.409 --> 07:59.312
shredding documents.

07:59.312 --> 08:01.148
- It's just preemptive.
They're just looking for--

08:01.148 --> 08:02.616
- Sergeant.

08:02.616 --> 08:04.184
- Where's the warrant?

08:09.623 --> 08:11.559
So you came here
with a hastily written

08:11.559 --> 08:14.562
and narrowly defined
search warrant to what?

08:14.562 --> 08:16.296
Upset my clients' patients?

08:16.296 --> 08:18.298
- Your client has been
diagnosing patients

08:18.298 --> 08:20.133
with cancer they don't have
to fleece them

08:20.133 --> 08:21.802
with treatments
they don't need.

08:21.802 --> 08:23.436
I'd say he's the one
upsetting them.

08:23.436 --> 08:25.038
- This is absurd.
[laughs]

08:25.038 --> 08:27.207
I have the highest cure rate
in the Midwest.

08:27.207 --> 08:29.977
My patients are every--

08:29.977 --> 08:32.179
- Dr. Reybold.

08:32.179 --> 08:34.313
Shredding client files.

08:34.313 --> 08:36.683
- I have nothing to hide,
Hank.

08:36.683 --> 08:38.051
- You two know each other?

08:38.051 --> 08:39.620
- I treated Sergeant Voight's
late wife.

08:39.620 --> 08:40.754
- Don't say another word.

08:40.754 --> 08:44.592
- You know who doesn't
shred files?

08:44.592 --> 08:45.893
Innocent people.

08:45.893 --> 08:48.161
- Hank, you know me.

08:48.161 --> 08:49.462
I held your wife's hand
when she--

08:49.462 --> 08:51.364
- Dr. Reybold.

08:51.364 --> 08:54.334
- Camille's death
was hard on me too.

08:54.334 --> 08:56.604
- Don't you say her name.
You hear me?

08:56.604 --> 08:57.971
- Back up, Sergeant.

08:57.971 --> 09:01.441
- She was such a fighter.

09:01.441 --> 09:04.812
She would not
want you to do this.

09:04.812 --> 09:08.348
[ominous music]

09:08.348 --> 09:10.050
- You're under arrest.
- Hank...

09:10.050 --> 09:13.486
- On what grounds?
- Obstruction of justice.

09:13.486 --> 09:15.088
We can pick him up
at the 21st.

09:15.088 --> 09:17.157
Cuff him.
- Get up.

09:17.157 --> 09:18.792
- Don't say anything
until I get there, Dean.

09:18.792 --> 09:20.728
- Hands behind your back.
- Shut it down.

09:25.666 --> 09:25.799
.

09:34.775 --> 09:35.142
[somber music]

09:37.711 --> 09:45.753
*

10:34.301 --> 10:37.971
- I told the detective
there was a gun.

10:37.971 --> 10:41.008
I don't know
what more I could do.

10:42.910 --> 10:44.511
- So that night...

10:44.511 --> 10:48.648
Ritchie took off on foot
after Roman shot him,

10:48.648 --> 10:51.719
but no car registered to him
was found here the next day.

10:51.719 --> 10:54.121
So I checked with Uber.
He doesn't have an account.

10:54.121 --> 10:55.555
No cabs came here,

10:55.555 --> 10:59.292
and his monthly el pass
doesn't have him on it all day.

10:59.292 --> 11:01.561
So...I'm wondering,

11:01.561 --> 11:04.131
did, maybe,
somebody drive him here?

11:06.599 --> 11:08.001
- Denny.

11:08.001 --> 11:09.402
- Ritchie's brother.

11:09.402 --> 11:12.605
- Ritchie had a couple DUIs
and had his license yanked.

11:12.605 --> 11:14.541
So, Denny,
he drove him around.

11:14.541 --> 11:16.243
- Okay, do you think
that Denny could have

11:16.243 --> 11:17.811
stayed when he came here?

11:17.811 --> 11:19.579
Waited for Ritchie to come out?

11:19.579 --> 11:21.081
- Maybe.

11:21.081 --> 11:24.752
Denny's--he's a good guy.

11:24.752 --> 11:27.587
- What's that
supposed to mean?

11:27.587 --> 11:31.624
- Just--just that...

11:31.624 --> 11:34.795
- Is there anything else
I should know, Callie?

11:34.795 --> 11:36.496
- No.

11:43.536 --> 11:45.072
[metal clanks]

11:50.577 --> 11:53.680
- You know, I don't know
if you remember,

11:53.680 --> 11:57.117
but when Camille used to see you
in your office--

11:57.117 --> 12:00.954
and this is...

12:00.954 --> 12:04.391
when she was at her lowest
from the pain of chemo--

12:06.259 --> 12:08.661
Well, you'd take her hand

12:08.661 --> 12:11.799
and tell her she should
just treasure every moment

12:11.799 --> 12:15.068
because life is so fragile.

12:15.068 --> 12:18.105
[ominous music]

12:18.105 --> 12:26.479
*

12:28.816 --> 12:32.152
You better start
enjoying every moment.

12:44.664 --> 12:46.199
- Two years ago,

12:46.199 --> 12:50.037
Dr. Reybold told me
I had bone cancer.

12:50.037 --> 12:51.504
He said it would be tough,

12:51.504 --> 12:54.842
but we'd get
through it together.

12:54.842 --> 12:57.310
The kind of chemo
he gave me,

12:57.310 --> 12:59.512
it rots your bones.

12:59.512 --> 13:01.849
- I couldn't stay at my job.

13:01.849 --> 13:04.151
I can't play
with my children,

13:04.151 --> 13:07.154
be with my husband.

13:07.154 --> 13:11.691
Dr. Reybold kept reassuring
that this chemo was gonna work.

13:11.691 --> 13:16.129
- I was alive.
It was a miracle.

13:16.129 --> 13:18.065
- A year ago,

13:18.065 --> 13:20.500
my teeth started falling out.

13:20.500 --> 13:24.471
Six months ago,
it took my leg.

13:24.471 --> 13:28.508
- And now you're telling me
it was all for money?

13:28.508 --> 13:31.578
[somber music]

13:31.578 --> 13:39.652
*

13:50.697 --> 13:52.532
- What have you got?
- I made you copies

13:52.532 --> 13:54.501
of the patient files
we could salvage.

13:54.501 --> 13:56.803
42 out of 57 patients.
All women.

13:56.803 --> 13:58.972
All poisoned
with chemo they did not need.

13:58.972 --> 14:01.041
All willing to testify.

14:01.041 --> 14:03.043
Is this enough?
- For fraud?

14:03.043 --> 14:05.078
- For homicide.

14:09.349 --> 14:11.584
- You want him
to stop practicing today?

14:11.584 --> 14:14.587
I go in front of a special
grand jury with fraud charges,

14:14.587 --> 14:16.656
and the Department
of Professional Regulations

14:16.656 --> 14:18.758
will pull his license
the minute I do.

14:18.758 --> 14:21.028
And when his lawyer
sees what we have,

14:21.028 --> 14:22.829
he'll roll.

14:22.829 --> 14:25.165
Look, you turn up
new information after that,

14:25.165 --> 14:26.934
we can go back
for another bite at the apple

14:26.934 --> 14:29.937
and use the fraud case
as evidence.

14:29.937 --> 14:33.140
Erin...
he stops practicing

14:33.140 --> 14:36.009
the minute I walk in.

14:38.111 --> 14:42.549
How's your sergeant?

14:42.549 --> 14:45.585
- He'll be a lot better
with a homicide conviction.

14:45.585 --> 14:47.287
[door opens]

14:53.560 --> 14:54.962
- [sighs]

14:56.229 --> 14:59.266
[cell phone buzzes]

15:07.207 --> 15:09.709
- Voight.

15:09.709 --> 15:11.979
What?

15:11.979 --> 15:14.982
[indistinct chatter]

15:16.216 --> 15:18.851
- Hey.
You made a deal?

15:18.851 --> 15:20.887
What kind of deal?

15:20.887 --> 15:23.090
- It's a year's
license suspension--

15:23.090 --> 15:24.992
- Are you kidding me?
- Five years probation,

15:24.992 --> 15:27.027
$14 million in resti--
- No jail time?

15:27.027 --> 15:28.761
- You think these women want
to get dragged through a trial?

15:28.761 --> 15:30.530
- I think those women
want justice.

15:30.530 --> 15:31.698
I do!

15:31.698 --> 15:34.201
- If he loses,
he could appeal for years.

15:34.201 --> 15:37.237
How many of them
have that kind of time?

15:37.237 --> 15:39.506
- He didn't just
defraud people, Dana.

15:39.506 --> 15:42.309
He murdered them.
- But we can't prove it.

15:42.309 --> 15:45.845
The judge advised us to take
this based on the evidence.

15:45.845 --> 15:47.180
State's attorney agreed.

15:47.180 --> 15:50.150
Until you get me new evidence...

15:50.150 --> 15:52.285
my hands are tied.

15:55.722 --> 15:58.725
[dramatic music]

15:58.725 --> 16:04.331
*

16:04.331 --> 16:06.033
- Hey.

16:16.076 --> 16:16.209
.

16:17.810 --> 16:18.311
- Well, at first blush,

16:19.379 --> 16:20.480
clinically,
classic psychopath.

16:20.480 --> 16:22.515
Prey on the weak.

16:22.515 --> 16:25.452
All these women are marginalized
by age or race

16:25.452 --> 16:28.488
and physically or emotionally
removed from any support.

16:28.488 --> 16:29.956
- Well, we know
from phone records

16:29.956 --> 16:31.658
four of these women
knew each other,

16:31.658 --> 16:33.226
and from there,

16:33.226 --> 16:35.162
we discovered
they met in a chat room,

16:35.162 --> 16:37.430
compared notes.

16:37.430 --> 16:40.500
They agreed to meet with him,
and as best we can tell,

16:40.500 --> 16:43.570
confront him about his methods.

16:43.570 --> 16:46.839
So my question is:

16:46.839 --> 16:48.075
how could he have managed
to pull them in for more rounds

16:48.075 --> 16:50.977
if they were already
skeptical?

16:50.977 --> 16:53.480
- Cancer diagnosis
