16:53.480 --> 16:55.415
People are looking for a guide

16:55.415 --> 16:57.084
through the process,

16:57.084 --> 16:58.318
someone they can trust.

16:58.318 --> 17:00.187
- A savior.

17:00.187 --> 17:01.954
- Hmm.

17:01.954 --> 17:03.990
And if they walked away,
what would they have?

17:03.990 --> 17:05.992
Psychopaths
control their victims

17:05.992 --> 17:08.161
to get that charge
they crave.

17:08.161 --> 17:09.929
Telling a healthy woman
she has cancer,

17:09.929 --> 17:11.198
oh, there's a thrill.

17:11.198 --> 17:13.665
Probably where he started.
Right?

17:13.665 --> 17:15.667
He does that,
doesn't get caught,

17:15.667 --> 17:17.737
so he escalates
to the next stimulus--

17:17.737 --> 17:20.006
treating her,
becoming her champion.

17:20.006 --> 17:22.474
I wager heavily
we look into this guy's past,

17:22.474 --> 17:25.112
there's mistreatment by women.

17:25.112 --> 17:27.380
Now he flipped it.

17:27.380 --> 17:29.549
"I used to be subject.

17:29.549 --> 17:32.219
Now I'm God."

17:32.219 --> 17:34.387
- Would you be willing
to testify to that?

17:34.387 --> 17:36.256
- [scoffs]

17:39.892 --> 17:43.130
In order to take the stand,
you know, I gotta...

17:43.130 --> 17:44.831
I get fully formed diagnosis,
right?

17:44.831 --> 17:47.767
Speak to him directly.

17:47.767 --> 17:49.469
- Well...

17:49.469 --> 17:52.139
he ain't pleading insanity...

17:52.139 --> 17:53.740
and I promise you

17:53.740 --> 17:57.377
his lawyer's not gonna
let you anywhere near him.

17:57.377 --> 17:59.045
