18:43.190 --> 18:44.857
I think you followed him,
and when he bled out

18:44.857 --> 18:46.226
you took his gun
so he'd look innocent.

18:46.226 --> 18:48.595
And because of that, a good
police officer is gonna go down

18:48.595 --> 18:50.930
for something he didn't do.
- You guys are incredible.

18:50.930 --> 18:52.098
- If you have that gun, Denny,

18:52.098 --> 18:53.500
you need to turn it over
right now.

18:53.500 --> 18:55.435
Otherwise, you're looking at--
- Are you arresting me?

18:56.569 --> 18:57.670
- Mm-mm, not yet.

18:57.670 --> 19:00.006
- I don't have a gun.

19:00.006 --> 19:01.774
I got nothing more
to say to you.

19:05.978 --> 19:07.380
- Thank you.

19:13.253 --> 19:15.054
- Whoa.

19:15.054 --> 19:16.523
You're that doctor
from the news.

19:16.523 --> 19:17.657
I'm sorry.

19:17.657 --> 19:20.793
Dr. Daniel Charles,
Chicago Med.

19:20.793 --> 19:23.930
Man, they sure are going after
us these days, aren't they?

19:23.930 --> 19:25.232
You out on bail?

19:25.232 --> 19:28.134
I mean, why are they even
charging you in the first place?

19:28.134 --> 19:30.237
Can you explain that to me?

19:32.839 --> 19:36.643
Must be so hard to distance
yourself from cancer patients.

19:36.643 --> 19:38.311
- When you got into
medicine,

19:38.311 --> 19:40.713
did you expect
to save everyone's life?

19:40.713 --> 19:42.582
- Hmm...

19:42.582 --> 19:44.884
but to lose patients
over and over,

19:44.884 --> 19:47.620
watch them get diminished
by illness...

19:47.620 --> 19:50.457
- The U.S. is so far behind.

19:50.457 --> 19:53.960
I have a series of cocktails
that are revolutionary.

19:53.960 --> 19:57.497
Other doctors don't approach
my methods or my numbers.

19:57.497 --> 19:59.165
That's what should be
on the news.

19:59.165 --> 20:01.634
- That should be on the news...
[both chuckle]

20:01.634 --> 20:03.135
And, of course, I mean,

20:03.135 --> 20:04.971
they never questioned
your therapies, right?

20:04.971 --> 20:06.539
I mean, wh--
- [chuckles]

20:06.539 --> 20:08.941
