20:53.786 --> 20:56.623
*

20:56.623 --> 20:58.124
- Hey.

20:58.124 --> 20:59.459
- Hey.

20:59.459 --> 21:00.927
- What do you know
about the brother?

21:00.927 --> 21:03.463
- Whose? Ritchie's?
- Yeah.

21:03.463 --> 21:05.332
- I didn't deal with him.
- I did some digging.

21:05.332 --> 21:07.834
He has two parking tickets
written on Callie's block.

21:07.834 --> 21:09.201
- Yeah, he'd drive Ritchie.

21:09.201 --> 21:11.371
- When Ritchie was in jail.

21:11.371 --> 21:12.739
Did Denny and Callie
have a thing?

21:12.739 --> 21:13.906
- How would I know?

21:13.906 --> 21:15.241
- There's something
going on there.

21:15.241 --> 21:16.876
She seemed
very protective of him.

21:16.876 --> 21:19.145
So I'm just trying
to figure out who to go at next.

21:19.145 --> 21:21.348
- So Denny took the gun.
- Yeah.

21:21.348 --> 21:23.082
- If he did, he'd have
thrown it in the river.

21:23.082 --> 21:25.918
Here we are.
Same place we started.

21:25.918 --> 21:28.688
- [scoffs]
That's defeatist.

21:28.688 --> 21:31.591
- No, that's realist.

21:31.591 --> 21:33.626
This is defeatist.

21:48.007 --> 21:49.376
- Thanks.

21:54.581 --> 21:56.115
[sighs]

21:56.115 --> 21:57.817
- [sighs]

21:59.386 --> 22:02.121
- Hank, I miss Camille.

22:03.923 --> 22:05.458
- Hmm.

22:09.396 --> 22:12.131
- I mean, my whole life
till I was 14 was Bunny.

22:12.131 --> 22:14.033
You know?

22:14.033 --> 22:16.903
When she was sober.
When she wasn't.

22:18.938 --> 22:21.207
I didn't know

22:21.207 --> 22:24.076
that moms could be kind.

22:24.076 --> 22:28.415
Or brave.
Or Unselfish.

22:29.649 --> 22:32.985
She didn't even like me
when you first brought me home.

22:32.985 --> 22:35.722
You remember that?
- Yeah.

22:35.722 --> 22:38.290
- She already had her hands
full with Justin,

22:38.290 --> 22:42.895
and I showed up and I just
doubled her trouble.

22:42.895 --> 22:45.932
[laughs]
We were hellions.

22:49.469 --> 22:52.739
I remember this one day
I came home...

22:52.739 --> 22:55.207
Iron Maiden T-shirt,
skirt up to here, you know,

22:55.207 --> 22:58.845
and she's just waiting for me
in the living room.

22:58.845 --> 23:02.482
She has a dress
from Marshall Field's.

23:05.452 --> 23:08.755
She told me that...

23:08.755 --> 23:11.958
you saw something in me
that was worth sacrificing for,

23:11.958 --> 23:16.028
and so she would too,

23:16.028 --> 23:20.166
and she used her Christmas money
to buy me that dress.

23:23.169 --> 23:24.971
- I have an idea.

23:24.971 --> 23:26.338
Reybold met with our victims

23:26.338 --> 23:28.741
three weeks before they
showed up dead or in comas.

23:28.741 --> 23:30.477
You have the accounts receivable
for his office?

23:30.477 --> 23:33.379
- Here and here.

23:33.379 --> 23:36.883
- The victims met with Reybold
on December 10th,

23:36.883 --> 23:39.318
and--there.

23:39.318 --> 23:41.788
December 11th...

23:41.788 --> 23:44.991
an order came into the office
for chemo for each victim.

23:44.991 --> 23:47.026
- How much?
- Twice as much as they got

23:47.026 --> 23:48.861
every other time before.

23:48.861 --> 23:50.096
- On the 11th?

23:50.096 --> 23:52.665
Wait,
'cause in Reybold's schedule,

23:52.665 --> 23:54.634
he has our victims
getting treated

23:54.634 --> 23:57.369
on December 14th,

23:57.369 --> 23:59.305
the 16th,

23:59.305 --> 24:01.073
and the 17th.

24:01.073 --> 24:05.044
And then he had
another order for chemo placed

24:05.044 --> 24:07.213
December 22nd

24:07.213 --> 24:10.149
for three times
the usual amount.

24:10.149 --> 24:12.318
And he's got them all listed
for appointments

24:12.318 --> 24:14.320
right after that.

24:14.320 --> 24:16.022
- Wait, what was the last order?

24:18.791 --> 24:20.693
- January 2nd.

24:20.693 --> 24:23.730
That's right before
they came into Med,

24:23.730 --> 24:26.766
and it's seven times
the usual amount.

24:28.367 --> 24:32.539
- How did he get that past
the insurance companies?

24:32.539 --> 24:35.575
They'd never approve seven times
the normal amount of chemo.

24:35.575 --> 24:38.110
- Did he even bill it
to insurance?

24:40.747 --> 24:42.414
- No.

24:42.414 --> 24:44.350
So his office
ate the payments?

24:44.350 --> 24:47.019
- Or he paid for it himself.

24:47.019 --> 24:49.455
If you're gonna order
enough chemo to kill someone,

24:49.455 --> 24:51.858
that would be murder.
- Is this enough?

24:53.425 --> 24:55.695
- His signature on the invoices

24:55.695 --> 24:57.363
proves intent
with physical evidence.

24:57.363 --> 24:59.899
Keeping it off the books
is a cover-up.

24:59.899 --> 25:02.334
If I can get the women
from the fraud case to testify

25:02.334 --> 25:06.072
he dosed them personally...

25:06.072 --> 25:08.207
I think we can convince a jury.

25:08.207 --> 25:10.209
- That's all I need to know.

25:10.209 --> 25:11.878
[applause]
- Thank you...thank you.

25:11.878 --> 25:14.714
You know, I've devoted
my whole life to healing,

25:14.714 --> 25:17.750
but healing is more than
finding the right medication,

25:17.750 --> 25:20.953
more than establishing
the right treatment program.

25:20.953 --> 25:22.889
[applause]
No, it's connecting

25:22.889 --> 25:24.624
with our patients wholly
and never giving up,

25:24.624 --> 25:28.360
making them believe that
a full recovery is possible too.

25:28.360 --> 25:30.830
- Yeah, is that how it went
with Jessica Pope?

25:30.830 --> 25:33.199
What about Dani Frank?
Carol Shepperd?

25:33.199 --> 25:34.433
- Back off.
- Leah Kamen?

25:34.433 --> 25:36.335
What about their healing?

25:36.335 --> 25:38.671
I guess they had a different
treatment program, huh, Doc?

25:38.671 --> 25:40.873
- Uh, this--this isn't--
- Turn around.

25:40.873 --> 25:42.441
You're under arrest
for the murder

25:42.441 --> 25:45.645
and attempted murder
of four patients.

25:45.645 --> 25:48.014
That's not too tight, is it?

25:48.014 --> 25:49.348
Come on.

25:49.348 --> 25:50.617
[crowd murmuring]

25:56.623 --> 25:56.723
.

25:57.624 --> 25:58.057
- These 42 patients

25:59.291 --> 26:00.426
already had their day
in court, Your Honor.

26:00.426 --> 26:03.062
Dr. Reybold took a plea
and was sentenced.

26:03.062 --> 26:05.231
Case closed.
- Except it's a straight line

26:05.231 --> 26:07.734
from the fraud to these murders,
and drawing that line--

26:07.734 --> 26:10.536
- Will unnecessarily
prejudice the jury.

26:10.536 --> 26:12.872
What happened to the patients
in that case

26:12.872 --> 26:14.440
is irrelevant
in the current proceeding.

26:14.440 --> 26:16.308
- Irrelevant?
Because the fraud victims

26:16.308 --> 26:18.144
didn't die and my victims did?

26:18.144 --> 26:20.112
- Your Honor--
- Pull it back, Ms. Shelby.

26:20.112 --> 26:23.282
- Dr. Reybold murdered four
women to cover up his fraud.

26:23.282 --> 26:25.217
The jury needs to hear this

26:25.217 --> 26:27.119
so that they can understand
the whole story.

26:27.119 --> 26:29.488
- But they'll be
unduly prejudiced if they do.

26:29.488 --> 26:30.790
The bottom line is:

26:30.790 --> 26:33.292
the fraud victims
can't testify.

26:41.668 --> 26:43.903
- Too prejudicial?
Not relevant?

26:43.903 --> 26:45.304
- It was an uphill battle.

26:45.304 --> 26:47.774
- So not one of the victims
can testify

26:47.774 --> 26:50.342
that Reybold dosed
our four women personally?

26:50.342 --> 26:52.111
- Three...the Medical Examiner

26:52.111 --> 26:55.514
just ruled Jessica Pope's death
a suicide.

26:55.514 --> 26:57.216
- Put me on the stand.

26:57.216 --> 26:58.685
- Why?
Do you have cancer?

26:58.685 --> 27:00.586
- I can walk a jury
through all of this.

27:00.586 --> 27:02.121
- Sure, then Green
will rip you a new one

27:02.121 --> 27:03.355
when she brings up Camille

27:03.355 --> 27:04.824
and your motive
for going after him.

27:04.824 --> 27:07.526
- I'm the lead investigator
on this case.

27:07.526 --> 27:10.296
If you don't put me
on the stand, she will,

27:10.296 --> 27:12.464
and you won't have
set the table for it.

27:12.464 --> 27:13.866
Dana.

27:13.866 --> 27:16.202
- If you go off script
one time,

27:16.202 --> 27:17.737
you will lose this case
for us.

27:17.737 --> 27:19.138
It is too big a risk.

27:19.138 --> 27:21.107
I'm putting Erin on
to talk about the investigation.

27:21.107 --> 27:24.143
There is no way
you are testifying.

27:30.582 --> 27:32.484
- If Denny's anything
like his brother,

27:32.484 --> 27:34.987
he would have thrown that gun
into the river like Roman said.

27:34.987 --> 27:36.723
- Denny's not like Ritchie
though.

27:36.723 --> 27:38.324
He's had the same job
for ten years.

27:38.324 --> 27:40.426
I mean, those parking tickets
by Callie's house--

27:40.426 --> 27:42.561
only brush with the law
he's ever had.

27:42.561 --> 27:46.265
I bet my life he took that gun
to protect Ritchie--and Callie.

27:46.265 --> 27:47.967
- So go talk to him.
- I can't.

27:47.967 --> 27:50.036
I have been
in this guy's face before.

27:50.036 --> 27:52.571
He won't roll for just me.
I mean, I-I need...

27:52.571 --> 27:53.973
something
to hold over him or--

27:53.973 --> 27:55.474
- I know what you need.

27:55.474 --> 27:56.976
- Wait, what?
- Me.

27:56.976 --> 27:59.445
Bobby, watch the desk.
I'm doing some field work.

27:59.445 --> 28:01.781
- Okay.
- Are you coming or what?

28:01.781 --> 28:02.882
- Yeah.

28:09.221 --> 28:10.656
- Hey.

28:10.656 --> 28:12.925
'Sup, Denny?

28:12.925 --> 28:14.761
- This is harassment.

28:14.761 --> 28:17.764
- I'm gonna paint you
a picture here, Denny.

28:17.764 --> 28:19.598
You lie to an officer,

28:19.598 --> 28:21.768
that's impeding
an investigation.

28:21.768 --> 28:23.870
You make a false statement
on the record,

28:23.870 --> 28:25.537
that's obstruction of
justice.

28:25.537 --> 28:26.973
You keep a gun,

28:26.973 --> 28:28.775
that's withholding evidence
in a murder.

28:28.775 --> 28:30.409
- You brought your mom?

28:30.409 --> 28:32.511
What, 'cause you couldn't prove
I did any of that on your own?

28:32.511 --> 28:34.446
- We have proof that you
drove your inebriated brother

28:34.446 --> 28:36.883
to a residence where he
committed aggravated battery,

28:36.883 --> 28:38.617
and then he threatened
a police officer,

28:38.617 --> 28:40.219
which led to his death.

28:40.219 --> 28:42.221
You know what you can
be charged with?

28:42.221 --> 28:43.589
Accessory to murder.

28:43.589 --> 28:44.891
- Whatever.

28:44.891 --> 28:46.292
You're just saying things
to try and trap me.

28:46.292 --> 28:47.794
- No, you will be charged

28:47.794 --> 28:49.962
as an accessory
in your own brother's death.

28:49.962 --> 28:52.198
Felony murder.
That's two to five years.

28:52.198 --> 28:54.666
And not in county.
Stateville.

28:54.666 --> 28:56.002
Come on, the way I see it,

28:56.002 --> 28:57.469
you've been trying to help
everybody else.

28:57.469 --> 28:59.305
Your brother.
Callie.

28:59.305 --> 29:02.541
If I were you, I'd start
thinking about helping myself.

29:02.541 --> 29:04.410
- Where's the gun, Denny?

29:07.313 --> 29:10.482
- That gun turns up, the city
does nothing for Callie.

29:10.482 --> 29:12.218
She quit her job
to take care of Andrew.

29:12.218 --> 29:14.453
Ritchie left her flat broke.

29:14.453 --> 29:17.456
She deserves better.

29:17.456 --> 29:18.858
- There's a reward

29:18.858 --> 29:21.593
for information leading
to the whereabouts of the gun.

29:21.593 --> 29:23.595
That reward could...

29:23.595 --> 29:26.698
take the turn of a check
made out to anonymous.

29:26.698 --> 29:29.701
If you tell the detective
in charge everything you saw--

29:29.701 --> 29:31.971
all of it--
and that gun turns back up,

29:31.971 --> 29:35.607
well, that check could end up
in the hands of a nice woman.

29:35.607 --> 29:38.210
25,000 dollars' worth.

29:38.210 --> 29:40.046
- And I wouldn't be charged
with anything?

29:40.046 --> 29:42.181
- You're the grieving brother.

29:42.181 --> 29:44.716
Why would we charge you
with anything?

29:49.989 --> 29:52.458
- In your review
of Dr. Reybold's books,

29:52.458 --> 29:55.261
you found no evidence he
billed any insurance companies

29:55.261 --> 29:57.864
for these treatments.
- No.

29:57.864 --> 30:01.400
- Well, who did pay
for these treatments?

30:01.400 --> 30:04.036
- Dr. Reybold himself.
From his personal account.

30:04.036 --> 30:05.204
- Personal.

30:05.204 --> 30:06.638
Which allowed him
to overdose patients--

30:06.638 --> 30:09.308
- Objection.
- Overruled.

30:09.308 --> 30:12.444
- To overdose patients
without raising a red flag

30:12.444 --> 30:15.347
with the insurance companies.
- Yes.

30:15.347 --> 30:18.284
- No further questions.

30:18.284 --> 30:20.853
- Could Dr. Reybold
have been helping patients

30:20.853 --> 30:22.621
get the care they needed?

30:22.621 --> 30:24.957
For instance,
if three patients came to him

30:24.957 --> 30:27.526
and said they were having
financial difficulties

30:27.526 --> 30:29.962
but wanted to stay alive...

30:29.962 --> 30:33.565
what kind of doctor might pay
for those treatments himself?

30:33.565 --> 30:37.003
- A really remarkable one.
That's for sure.

30:39.771 --> 30:42.808
- Thank you.
That's all.

30:42.808 --> 30:44.776
- My conversation
with Dr. Reybold

30:44.776 --> 30:46.578
coupled with
a look at his history

30:46.578 --> 30:50.582
led me to a clear diagnosis
of psychopathy.

30:50.582 --> 30:56.188
The psychopathic mind
lacks fear, remorse, empathy.

30:56.188 --> 31:00.960
In essence, it can't connect to
or care about others.

31:00.960 --> 31:02.929
That's Dr. Reybold.

31:02.929 --> 31:04.530
- But he's a doctor.

31:04.530 --> 31:07.066
Doesn't that suggest
empathy or caring?

31:07.066 --> 31:09.969
- Well, you'd be shocked
how many functional psychopaths

31:09.969 --> 31:11.303
are in the world,

31:11.303 --> 31:13.539
you know, attracted to power,
control.

31:13.539 --> 31:15.574
Flaunting
his success rates,

31:15.574 --> 31:18.810
the therapies only
he can administer,

31:18.810 --> 31:22.781
belittling his patients
to keep them under his control.

31:22.781 --> 31:25.617
"I'm the one
with the medical degree,"

31:25.617 --> 31:27.653
he would say to his patients.

31:27.653 --> 31:29.421
- You know this how?

31:29.421 --> 31:30.622
- Because he told me.

31:30.622 --> 31:33.492
- I renew my objection.
This entire conversation--

31:33.492 --> 31:37.163
- Was a spontaneous admission
that has already been ruled on.

31:37.163 --> 31:38.965
- Agreed.
Overruled.

31:38.965 --> 31:40.099
Continue, Ms. Shelby.

31:40.099 --> 31:43.169
- So Dr. Reybold
would ask his patients

31:43.169 --> 31:44.971
if they had a medical degree?

31:44.971 --> 31:47.739
- And made sure they knew

31:47.739 --> 31:50.609
he was the only one
who could save them.

31:50.609 --> 31:53.445
Those are actual words
from our conversation.

31:53.445 --> 31:56.315
- Thank you, Dr. Charles.

31:58.050 --> 32:01.653
- Well, let's talk
about that conversation.

32:01.653 --> 32:04.223
Was it at your office?
- No.

32:04.223 --> 32:06.392
- At the court?
Ordered by a judge?

32:06.392 --> 32:08.227
- Nope.
- Did Dr. Reybold know

32:08.227 --> 32:09.996
he was being interviewed?

32:09.996 --> 32:12.164
- As I said before,
it was not an interview.

32:12.164 --> 32:15.134
It was two doctors striking up
a conversation.

32:15.134 --> 32:17.269
- Where did this conversation
take place?

32:17.269 --> 32:20.306
- In a coffee shop.
- Near your house?

32:20.306 --> 32:22.341
- No.
- Your office?

32:22.341 --> 32:24.243
- No.
- In fact,

32:24.243 --> 32:28.014
it was 8 miles
from either of those places.

32:29.081 --> 32:30.816
- Didn't measure.

32:30.816 --> 32:32.384
- Do you know
how many coffee shops

32:32.384 --> 32:35.054
are between your house
or office and there?

32:35.054 --> 32:36.722
- I don't.

32:36.722 --> 32:38.357
- 37.

32:38.357 --> 32:41.327
37 other coffee shops,

32:41.327 --> 32:44.030
and you rolled
into this particular one,

32:44.030 --> 32:46.598
two blocks
from the defendant's house?

32:46.598 --> 32:49.301
To stalk him?
- Objection.

32:49.301 --> 32:50.602
- Sustained.

32:50.602 --> 32:52.704
- Were you paid
by the prosecution

32:52.704 --> 32:54.373
for your services,
Dr. Charles?

32:54.373 --> 32:55.441
- I was not.

32:55.441 --> 32:58.044
- You're an unpaid agent
of the police.

32:58.044 --> 33:01.247
- No one told me
to speak with Dr. Reybold.

33:01.247 --> 33:05.051
I walked into that coffee shop

33:05.051 --> 33:07.519
and I saw this...

33:07.519 --> 33:09.388
doctor...

33:10.622 --> 33:12.658
And my curiosity
got the best of me.

33:12.658 --> 33:14.860
- That works out well for State,
doesn't it?

33:14.860 --> 33:16.262
Withdrawn.

33:17.729 --> 33:19.598
Ever socialize with members

33:19.598 --> 33:22.101
of the Intelligence Unit,
Dr. Charles?

33:22.101 --> 33:24.303
Perhaps at a bar called Molly's?

33:24.303 --> 33:27.073
- I have.
- So they're friends of yours?

33:27.073 --> 33:29.775
- My report on Dr. Reybold
is an unbiased analy--

33:29.775 --> 33:31.710
- That wasn't the question.

33:31.710 --> 33:33.945
- I know them through work

33:33.945 --> 33:37.216
and would be very proud
to call them my friends.

33:37.216 --> 33:38.817
- No further questions.

33:38.817 --> 33:41.787
[dramatic music]

33:41.787 --> 33:46.092
*

33:46.092 --> 33:48.894
- Look, get a continuance.
My team and I--

33:48.894 --> 33:52.098
- I already used up my goodwill
with this judge.

33:52.098 --> 33:53.865
- Then put Antonio
on the stand.

33:53.865 --> 33:55.567
He'll testify to the paper trail
of the money.

33:55.567 --> 33:56.868
- The damage has been done.

33:56.868 --> 33:59.371
They'll make those payments
look like something else.

33:59.371 --> 34:01.507
Again.

34:01.507 --> 34:04.876
- So tell me
what you need to win.

34:06.011 --> 34:09.981
- I need the patients
from the fraud case back in.

34:09.981 --> 34:12.484
I need 42 people
on a witness stand

34:12.484 --> 34:14.018
to say he dosed them
personally

34:14.018 --> 34:15.654
or any eyewitness

34:15.654 --> 34:18.389
that can put that needle
in Reybold's hand.

34:18.389 --> 34:20.426
Can you do that?

34:20.426 --> 34:22.128
- Maybe.

34:24.330 --> 34:26.697
If you put me on the stand.

34:29.801 --> 34:32.003
All three victims were
in contact with each other,

34:32.003 --> 34:33.205
comparing notes.

34:33.205 --> 34:35.206
We know this from
their phone records.

34:35.206 --> 34:38.677
After their December 10th
meeting with Dr. Reybold,

34:38.677 --> 34:40.779
they agreed
to an experimental treatment

34:40.779 --> 34:42.547
which, in actuality,

34:42.547 --> 34:46.485
was simply
twice the usual dose of chemo.

34:46.485 --> 34:49.987
The following week, he upped it
to three times the amount.

34:49.987 --> 34:52.056
By the time they wound up
in the hospital,

34:52.056 --> 34:53.391
it was at seven times.

34:53.391 --> 34:56.161
- Because they confronted him
about what he did,

34:56.161 --> 34:57.796
and he was afraid
of being exposed.

34:57.796 --> 35:00.199
- Objection.
Counsel is testifying.

35:00.199 --> 35:02.601
- Sustained.

35:02.601 --> 35:04.370
- In your investigation,

35:04.370 --> 35:05.737
did you find it suspicious

35:05.737 --> 35:08.374
three patients met with
the doctor one day--

35:08.374 --> 35:09.441
- Objection.

35:09.441 --> 35:11.577
No one knows what transpired
in this meeting.

35:11.577 --> 35:15.181
- That's because everyone in
that meeting besides Dr. Reybold

35:15.181 --> 35:16.648
is dead or in a coma.

35:16.648 --> 35:18.384
- You Honor.
- One more time,

35:18.384 --> 35:21.019
and you're in contempt.

35:21.019 --> 35:23.455
- [sighs]

35:23.455 --> 35:26.858
Could the amounts the patients
received have been lab mistakes?

35:26.858 --> 35:29.795
- No, Dr. Reybold's signature
was on every order.

35:29.795 --> 35:31.730
- Well, what about
a dosing error?

35:31.730 --> 35:33.465
- His staffer testified

35:33.465 --> 35:36.402
that Dr. Reybold personally
administered those doses.

35:36.402 --> 35:38.036
- But the staffer cut a deal.

35:38.036 --> 35:39.271
- That doesn't mean
it wasn't the truth.

35:39.271 --> 35:41.473
- Objection.
Improper opinion.

35:41.473 --> 35:42.808
- Sustained.

35:42.808 --> 35:44.876
- What about any
other witnesses who--

35:44.876 --> 35:46.312
- Asked and answered.

35:46.312 --> 35:48.580
- Yes, Ms. Shelby,
move on.

35:48.580 --> 35:52.384
- Your Honor, someone has to
speak for these victims.

35:52.384 --> 35:54.753
- You don't speak.
You ask questions.

35:54.753 --> 35:56.488
And if nobody else
saw the doctor dosing--

35:56.488 --> 35:59.691
- Someone else did.

35:59.691 --> 36:02.361
Me.

36:02.361 --> 36:05.631
I saw Dr. Reybold
dose a patient.

36:05.631 --> 36:07.766
My wife.

36:07.766 --> 36:10.369
I saw Dr. Reybold
dose my wife Camille

36:10.369 --> 36:14.005
who died of cancer
under Dr. Reybold's care

36:22.281 --> 36:22.414
.

36:23.315 --> 36:24.049
- Sergeant Voight--
- I'm a witness.

36:24.950 --> 36:27.953
I saw him dose a patient.

36:29.555 --> 36:31.823
- The State has
no further questions

36:31.823 --> 36:33.559
for this witness.

36:35.261 --> 36:37.563
- Well, I have a few.

36:41.433 --> 36:43.702
Losing your wife to cancer

36:43.702 --> 36:46.405
must have been very painful,
Sergeant.

36:49.641 --> 36:53.011
Can you talk
about your wife's illness?

36:58.850 --> 37:02.053
- Camille was referred
to Dr. Reybold

37:02.053 --> 37:05.291
when her ovarian cancer
returned.

37:05.291 --> 37:11.297
He recommended
an aggressive course

37:11.297 --> 37:14.933
and then a second round
when that didn't get it all.

37:14.933 --> 37:17.636
She was cold all the time...

37:19.638 --> 37:22.974
Couldn't keep food down.

37:22.974 --> 37:26.878
Memory went in and out.
She...

37:26.878 --> 37:29.581
She was depressed.

37:32.751 --> 37:36.121
She fought as hard
as she could, but...

37:37.122 --> 37:39.157
- She sounds brave.

37:41.860 --> 37:44.062
- She was.

37:44.062 --> 37:45.731
- [sighs]

37:45.731 --> 37:47.599
You're still in mourning

37:47.599 --> 37:50.636
over your wife's death.

37:50.636 --> 37:53.204
Isn't that what this is
about?

37:53.204 --> 37:54.773
- No.

37:56.342 --> 37:58.444
- How gratifying would it be

37:58.444 --> 38:01.880
to help convict Dr. Reybold?

38:01.880 --> 38:03.915
- It would be very gratifying.

38:03.915 --> 38:05.917
- No further questions.
- For all his victims.

38:05.917 --> 38:07.453
- I said no further questions.

38:07.453 --> 38:10.489
You answered exactly
as I expected you to.

38:12.190 --> 38:13.892
- Redirect?

38:15.427 --> 38:18.063
What other victims

38:18.063 --> 38:20.231
are you referring to,
Sergeant Voight?

38:20.231 --> 38:21.433
- Objection.

38:21.433 --> 38:23.502
- Ms. Green
questioned my witness

38:23.502 --> 38:27.839
about one prior patient,
Camille Voight.

38:27.839 --> 38:29.207
Now she opened the door

38:29.207 --> 38:32.978
to the other 42 patients
he treated.

38:32.978 --> 38:35.447
- She's right.
Overruled.

38:36.948 --> 38:39.284
- What other victims?

38:39.284 --> 38:42.388
- Helen Graham...

38:42.388 --> 38:44.723
Nia Felten...

38:44.723 --> 38:47.493
Priya Parvati...

38:47.493 --> 38:49.928
Anne Gamerman...

38:49.928 --> 38:52.398
and 38 other people

38:52.398 --> 38:56.101
this doctor diagnosed
with cancer they didn't have

38:56.101 --> 38:58.404
and treated with chemo
they didn't need.

38:58.404 --> 38:59.738
- And how do you know this
to be true?

38:59.738 --> 39:03.241
- Because he said so himself
in court under oath.

39:03.241 --> 39:05.176
- Objection.
- Overruled.

39:05.176 --> 39:06.712
Continue.

39:08.414 --> 39:11.149
- Dr. Reybold confessed

39:11.149 --> 39:15.153
to personally poisoning
42 patients,

39:15.153 --> 39:18.056
ruining their lives,

39:18.056 --> 39:20.426
terrifying them
and their families,

39:20.426 --> 39:22.428
and he did it all for a payout,

39:22.428 --> 39:24.630
and he admitted to all of this

39:24.630 --> 39:26.164
as part of a deal he made

39:26.164 --> 39:29.735
with the State of Illinois,
copping to fraud.

39:32.838 --> 39:36.475
- This deal, Sergeant Voight?

39:36.475 --> 39:37.943
- That's the one.

39:37.943 --> 39:39.545
- The State would like
to enter into evidence

39:39.545 --> 39:42.548
case number 111 496

39:42.548 --> 39:46.852
and amend its witness list
by 42 people.

39:46.852 --> 39:50.021
[dramatic music]

39:50.021 --> 39:59.631
*

40:02.634 --> 40:04.936
- They have a verdict.

40:04.936 --> 40:09.274
- Hour of deliberation.
That's...

40:09.274 --> 40:11.142
that's probably good, right?

40:12.978 --> 40:15.280
- Camille would be proud
of you.

40:18.750 --> 40:21.286
- You too, kiddo.

40:23.054 --> 40:25.557
- On the count
of Narcotic Induced Homicide

40:25.557 --> 40:27.158
of Danielle Frank...

40:27.158 --> 40:29.861
- We find the defendant
guilty.

40:29.861 --> 40:32.464
- On the count of Narcotic
Induced Attempted Homicide

40:32.464 --> 40:33.832
of Carol Shepperd...

40:33.832 --> 40:35.834
- We find the defendant guilty.

40:35.834 --> 40:38.570
- On the count of Narcotic
Induced Attempted Homicide

40:38.570 --> 40:39.838
of Leah Kamen...

40:39.838 --> 40:42.340
- We find the defendant guilty.

40:42.340 --> 40:44.743
- Defendant is remanded
into custody until such time

40:44.743 --> 40:46.878
as a sentencing hearing
is scheduled.

40:46.878 --> 40:49.047
Bailiff.

40:49.047 --> 40:52.751
- Hank, your wife
did not suffer needlessly.

40:52.751 --> 40:54.986
You have to believe me.
The cancer did come back.

40:54.986 --> 40:56.387
I never harmed Camille.

40:56.387 --> 40:58.490
These patients,
I was their only hope.

40:58.490 --> 41:00.125
They got years because of me.

41:00.125 --> 41:03.261
You can't put someone away
for saving lives.

41:03.261 --> 41:05.130
You can't!

41:05.130 --> 41:07.398
I wasn't harming them.
I was helping them.

41:07.398 --> 41:09.434
Helping!

41:14.372 --> 41:16.374
- Look, you're swimming!
You're swimming!

41:16.374 --> 41:17.809
That was so good.
Did you see that?

41:17.809 --> 41:19.611
- [laughs]
Yeah.

41:19.611 --> 41:21.547
- I'm swimming!
- You sure are.

41:21.547 --> 41:22.814
- Whoo!

41:22.814 --> 41:24.215
He's gonna get you.

41:24.215 --> 41:25.784
- How did that feel?
- Swimming!

41:25.784 --> 41:28.319
- You sure were.
He was holding on to my suit.

41:28.319 --> 41:31.557
That's awesome.

41:31.557 --> 41:33.058
- S!
- [murmurs]

41:33.058 --> 41:34.660
T!

41:34.660 --> 41:36.461
What's the T say?

41:36.461 --> 41:38.063
Tuh, tuh, tuh, tuh.

41:38.063 --> 41:39.565
Good.
What's this letter?

41:39.565 --> 41:40.932
- U.
- U.

41:40.932 --> 41:43.301
You want Dad to open a present?
Let Dad open a present.

41:43.301 --> 41:45.403
Give it to Dad.
Give it to Dad.

41:45.403 --> 41:49.374
This is for Dad.
- Here, Mommy, you can film.

41:49.374 --> 41:51.577
Okay, you gonna help me?

41:51.577 --> 41:53.111
- Yeah, I can help you.
- Help me.

41:58.584 --> 41:59.985
- Hi, honey.
- There's Mama.

41:59.985 --> 42:02.621
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas.

42:02.621 --> 42:05.456
- I love you.
- I love you.

42:05.456 --> 42:08.459
[somber music]

